sql:
SELECT MAX(validation_date)
FROM data_validation
WHERE nutrition_id = 0;

SELECT category_name
FROM caloric_intake_categories
WHERE category_id = 1;

SELECT MAX(value) AS max_caloric_intake
FROM nutrition_data
WHERE country_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(value) AS average_caloric_intake
FROM nutrition_data
WHERE country_id = 0;

SELECT source_abbreviation
FROM nutrition_data_sources
WHERE source_name = 'World Health Organization';

SELECT category_id, value
FROM nutrition_data
WHERE country_id = 1 AND year_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- Cumulative caloric intake refers to the total amount of calories consumed over a period of time; 
- Validated nutrition data refers to data that has been verified for accuracy; 
- Audited nutrition data refers to data that has been reviewed for quality and reliability; 
- Health outcomes include life expectancy, mortality rates, and vaccination rates; 
- Demographics include population, urbanization rate, median age, gender ratio, and age distribution.
